      <li>Balance carbon and nitrogen: Feed a balance of nitrogen-rich foods (e.g., food scraps) and carbon-rich materials (e.g., cardboard).</li>
      <li>Avoid overfeeding: Feed in small amounts regularly. Overfeeding can lead to excess food that decomposes too slowly.</li>
      <li>Keep it moist: Ensure the food is moist but not too wet. The ideal moisture is like a wrung-out sponge.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

